1. Download Visual Studio Code Editor https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Make sure that Node.js is installed on the computer. If not, I provided the link here --> https://nodejs.org/en/download/

3. As soon as you set up points 1 & 2, open the project using the terminal. Click on terminal and new terminal. make sure you are in the path of the project: cd 'D:\Angular\React\project' and click enter.

4. To launch the project type this command: npm start

5. To launch tests type this command: npm tests

 

(The tests have been provided to explain how I would Mock an API using the Jest Library. You can find them here. App.test.js)
